<h1>CLI Gem Data Project Tips</h1>

<p>If you're anything like me, you're probably terrified of starting the CLI Data Gem project. Your palms get sweaty, your mind is racing, and you're basically memorizing Avi's CLI Walkthrough video. Let me attempt to help you out with some basic tips:</p>

<p>
<ol>
<li>Picking a Website That is Easy To Scrape <br>
Before starting out, I would poke around different sites to find one that has clean and organized code. If you‚Äôre not sure, ask someone (see advice #4).

<li>Throw Out Advice #1 if You‚Äôre Absolutely Passionate About Your Chosen Website <br>
With that said, the website I chose to scrape was a NIGHTMARE. However, I decided to use this project to contribute to my side hustle. It took me (way) longer than normal but I didn‚Äôt want to give up or pick a new site because I really (like really) want to scrape that data! In the end, your passion and your hustle will take you to the finish line even if the website contains iframes, dynamic URLs, and headaches for days. </li>

<li>Start Small <br>
You know how people like to say ‚ÄúGo big or go home‚Äù? Yea, that doesn‚Äôt apply here. It is much easier to start small and grow from there instead of attempting something big, creating something that is messy or doesn‚Äôt work, and wasting time. Not that I have any personal experience with this...<br></li>

